journal_text: Today I learned about Python lists and dictionaries. I found lists easy to use but struggled with dictionary methods.
I tried writing a function to calculate the factorial of a number, but I'm confused about recursive calls.
Explored object-oriented programming today. Classes and inheritance seem straightforward, but I have doubts about polymorphism.
Worked on NumPy arrays and operations. I think I understand broadcasting, but I need more practice.
Debugged my code using print statements. It worked, but I want to learn better debugging tools.
